Flask Blog API Documentation
1. Overview
This API allows users to:

Register and log in with JWT authentication.

Create blog posts.

View all posts.

Update or delete their own posts.

2. Endpoints
üîë Authentication
POST /register  
Registers a new user.
Body (JSON):

json
{
  "username": "sai",
  "password": "mypassword"
}
Response:

json
{"msg": "User registered successfully"}
POST /login  
Logs in and returns a JWT token.
Body (JSON):

json
{
  "username": "sai",
  "password": "mypassword"
}
Response:

json
{"access_token": "<JWT_TOKEN>"}
üìù Posts
POST /posts  
Creates a new post (requires JWT).
Headers:

Code
Authorization: Bearer <JWT_TOKEN>
Body (JSON):

json
{
  "title": "My First Blog Post",
  "content": "This is my very first post."
}
Response:

json
{"msg": "Post created"}
GET /posts  
Retrieves all posts.
Response:

json
[
  {
    "id": 1,
    "user_id": 2,
    "title": "My First Blog Post",
    "content": "This is my very first post.",
    "created_at": "2026-02-26T08:54:00"
  }
]
PUT /posts/<post_id>  
Updates a post (requires JWT, only owner can update).
Headers:

Code
Authorization: Bearer <JWT_TOKEN>
Body (JSON):

json
{
  "title": "Updated Title",
  "content": "Updated Content"
}
Response:

json
{"msg": "Post updated"}
DELETE /posts/<post_id>  
Deletes a post (requires JWT, only owner can delete).
Headers:

Code
Authorization: Bearer <JWT_TOKEN>
Response:

json
{"msg": "Post deleted"}
3. Testing Steps
Start Flask app  
Run:

bash
python app.py
Open http://127.0.0.1:5000/.

Register a user  
Fill in username/password ‚Üí click Register.

Login  
Enter credentials ‚Üí click Login.
Token is saved in token variable.

Create a post  
Enter title/content ‚Üí click Create Post.

Load posts  
Click Load Posts ‚Üí see all posts with IDs.

Update a post

Open browser console (F12 ‚Üí Console).

Paste:

js
fetch("/posts/1", {
    method: "PUT",
    headers: {
        "Content-Type": "application/json",
        "Authorization": "Bearer " + token
    },
    body: JSON.stringify({
        title: "Updated Title",
        content: "Updated Content"
    })
}).then(res => res.json()).then(console.log);
Delete a post

In console, paste:

js
fetch("/posts/1", {
    method: "DELETE",
    headers: {
        "Authorization": "Bearer " + token
    }
}).then(res => res.json()).then(console.log);
Verify  
Click Load Posts again ‚Üí confirm changes.
